@startuml
title Hardware Team SOP â€“ Electrical Documentation & Failure Analysis

start

:Receive Hardware Failure Information;
note right
Source:
- Production
- Service Team
- Customer Complaint
end note

:Record Failure Details;
:Analyze Root Cause;

if (Repeated Failure?) then (Yes)

    :Collect Failure Data;
    :Analyze Power Quality;
   
    if (Power Issue?) then (Yes)
        :Identify Voltage / Ground / Spike Issues;
        :Recommend Improvements;
        :Coordinate with Electrical Team;
    else (No)
        :Analyze Mounting Method;
        :Review Design;
        :Modify Clamp / 3D Design;
    endif

else (No)
   
    :Collect Failed Component;
    :Perform Functional Testing;
   
    if (Component Functional?) then (Yes)
        :Close Case;
    else (No)
        :Verify Warranty Status;
        :Initiate Warranty Claim;
        :Record Results;
    endif

endif

:Perform Root Cause Analysis (5 Why);

:Evaluate Alternative Components;

if (Management Approval?) then (Approved)
   
    :Procure Sample Components;
    :Perform Hardware Testing;
    :Validate Functional Requirements;
    :Conduct Field Trial;

    if (Field Trial Successful?) then (Yes)
        :Finalize Solution;
        :Update Documentation;
        :Implement Full Scale;
    else (No)
        :Re-evaluate Component;
    endif

else (Rejected)
    :Select Alternative Component;
endif

:Maintain Records;
note right
Records include:
- Electrical Drawings
- Failure Reports
- RCA Documents
- Warranty Records
- Validation Reports
end note

:Monitor KPIs;
note right
KPIs:
- Failure Rate Reduction
- Resolution Time
- Warranty Success Rate
end note

stop
@enduml



